  "key_findings": [
    "USD prices have NEVER increased for an existing tier amount. EA has only restructured which tiers exist.",
    "The FIFA 23 restructure (Sept 2022) was the only major structural change in the 7-year period studied.",
    "The June 2023 mid-year price increase affected non-USD currencies only (GBP, AUD, CAD, etc.) citing currency valuation changes.",
    "EA's strategy has been to push spend ceilings higher (from $39.99 max to $149.99 max) rather than raise per-point costs.",
    "The cost-per-point at the maximum tier has actually decreased over time: $0.00869 (FIFA 19) to $0.00811 (FC 26).",
    "The 8-tier structure (100/500/1050/1600/2800/5900/12000/18500) started with FIFA 23 in September 2022.",
    "The rebrand from FIFA Points to FC Points in FC 24 (2023) was cosmetic only - no pricing impact."
  ]
